                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2001-03-23</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>This was a great reference to start an Information Security Architecture project. There are many guidelines, procedures and forms that take the guess work out of the administration of such a project. The book is great at keeping you on track with your security objectives. I have found that it is so easy with such large projects to lose sight of the objectives. Security is not only technical assessments of the network and operating components but also a combination of management and administration of personnel, policies and procedures and continuous application of pressure to meeting the security requirements of an organization. This book provides excellent value for the price.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Very Informative</div>
                    <div>
